"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s20",
"title":{
"__html":"Hypoxemic Respiratory Failure"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c69202",
"children":[
"Hypoxemic Respiratory Failure"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s20_0",
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0724b5",
"children":[
"Hypoxemic respiratory failure is caused by inadequate oxygenation of hemoglobin. The most common causes of hypoxic respiratory failure in the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intensive care unit",
"children":[
"ICU"
]
},
" are ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"ventilation/perfusion ratio",
"children":[
"V/Q"
]
},
" mismatch (or shunt, when V/Q = 0), which occurs when perfused areas of the lung are not ventilated."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s20_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7309e7",
"children":[
"Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"618dad",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute respiratory distress syndrome",
"children":[
"ARDS"
]
},
" is a syndrome of hypoxemic respiratory failure presenting as noncardiogenic pulmonary edema. Precipitating causes of ARDS include pulmonary infection, hemorrhagic shock, pancreatitis, trauma, transfusions, and sepsis."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s20_inline_t1",
"mk19_bb_pm_s20_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s20_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"730143",
"children":[
"Optimal mechanical ventilation associated with the prevention of ventilator-associated lung injury includes:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8983d4",
"children":[
"lung-protective ventilation using volume-controlled ventilation with a tidal volume of 4 to 8 mL/kg of ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"ideal body weight "
]
},
"(low tidal volume)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bff769",
"children":[
"plateau (end-inspiratory) pressure <30 cm H",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"O (even if this results in “permissive” hypercapnia and acidosis)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e17acc",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"positive end-expiratory pressure",
"children":[
"PEEP"
]
},
" "
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"862560",
"children":[
"Limiting IV fluids and using diuretics to keep ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"central venous pressure",
"children":[
"CVP"
]
},
" at lower targets has been associated with a more rapid improvement in lung function but no effect on mortality."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"da1877",
"children":[
"Use of prone positioning in severe ARDS has a mortality benefit."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4f6f9d",
"children":[
"Glucocorticoids are not indicated for the acute treatment of ARDS."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s20_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c016fd",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 55-year-old woman with acute pancreatitis has increasingly severe shortness of breath for 12 hours. She has no history of cardiac disease. Pulse rate is 116/min, respiration rate is 40/min, and arterial O",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" saturation is 86% (on supplemental oxygen). Diffuse bilateral crackles are heard. Chest x-ray shows diffuse airspace disease. She is intubated and mechanically ventilated. With an F",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"IO"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" of 1.0, her arterial P",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"O"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" is 150 mm Hg."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c11e7c",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose moderate ARDS. For management, select a tidal volume of 4 to 8 mL/kg of ideal body weight."
]
}
]
}
]
},
